  ('CISA-00009', 5, 'Medium', 'Vulnerability Management', 'An organization''s vulnerability management program includes regular scanning, but the auditor discovers that remediation efforts are consistently delayed due to a lack of clearly defined roles and responsibilities. Which of the following recommendations is MOST appropriate for the auditor to make?', 'Implement a risk-based prioritization scheme for vulnerability remediation.', 'Increase the frequency of vulnerability scans to identify issues faster.', 'Develop and document a vulnerability remediation policy with defined roles and timelines.', 'Procure a more advanced vulnerability scanning tool with automated remediation capabilities.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Develop and document a vulnerability remediation policy with defined roles and timelines.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCO