  ('CISA-00010', 5, 'Medium', 'Physical Security', 'During a review of a data center''s physical security, the IS auditor observes that the emergency exit doors are propped open to improve air circulation. Which of the following should the auditor recommend as the MOST appropriate corrective action?', 'Implement security awareness training to educate employees about the importance of physical security.', 'Install an alarm system that triggers when emergency exit doors are opened.', 'Install an alternative air circulation system to eliminate the need to prop open the doors.', 'Issue a policy prohibiting employees from propping open the emergency exit doors.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Install an alternative air circulation system to eliminate the need to prop open the doors.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong: 