  ('CISA-00060', 2, 'Medium', 'IT Performance Monitoring', 'During a review of IT service level agreements (SLAs), an IS auditor identifies that key performance indicators (KPIs) related to system availability are consistently met, but user satisfaction is low. What should the IS auditor do FIRST?', 'Recommend increasing the target for system availability in the SLAs.', 'Evaluate the relevance of the current KPIs and their alignment with user needs.', 'Review the incident management process to identify recurring issues.', 'Suggest conducting a user satisfaction survey to gather more detailed feedback.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Evaluate the relevance of the current KPIs and their alignment with user needs.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Recommend increasing the target for system availability i