  ('CISA-00073', 5, 'Medium', 'Data Loss Prevention (DLP)', 'During a CISA review of a company''s DLP implementation, the auditor discovers that the DLP system generates a high volume of alerts, many of which are false positives. This is causing security analysts to ignore alerts, potentially overlooking genuine data breaches. What is the MOST important action for the auditor to recommend?', 'Review the DLP system''s configuration and tuning to reduce the false positive rate.', 'Recommend the immediate replacement of the current DLP system with a more accurate solution.', 'Advise increasing the number of security analysts to handle the high volume of alerts.', 'Suggest implementing mandatory training for all employees on data handling policies.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Review the DLP system''s configuration and tuning to reduce the false positive rate.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purpo