  ('CISA-00074', 5, 'Medium', 'Data Encryption', 'An auditor is reviewing an organization''s data encryption practices. They discover that the database containing customer Personally Identifiable Information (PII) is encrypted at rest using a weak encryption algorithm that is known to be vulnerable to brute-force attacks. What is the MOST appropriate recommendation for the auditor to make?', 'Recommend the implementation of stronger access controls to the database.', 'Advise the organization to immediately upgrade to a more robust encryption algorithm.', 'Suggest implementing a data masking solution in addition to the existing encryption.', 'Report the finding to senior management and recommend conducting a risk assessment.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Advise the organization to immediately upgrade to a more robust encryption algorithm.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for futu