  ('CISA-00218', 1, 'Hard', 'Audit Standards and Regulations', 'During an IS audit of a financial institution, the auditor discovers that the institution is processing a significant volume of cross-border wire transfers without adequate monitoring for compliance with anti-money laundering (AML) regulations. Which of the following actions should the IS auditor take to BEST address this finding?', 'Report the finding to the regulatory authorities immediately, as required by mandatory reporting laws.', 'Assess the potential financial and reputational impact of non-compliance and include this information in the audit report.', 'Recommend that management implement a robust AML monitoring system and conduct retrospective reviews of past transactions.', 'Extend the audit scope to include a detailed review of all aspects of the institution''s compliance program.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Assess the potential financial and reputational impact of non-compliance and include this information in the audit report.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you 