  ('CISA-00230', 4, 'Medium', 'Data Backup and Recovery', 'An organization''s backup and recovery procedures specify daily incremental backups and weekly full backups. The IS auditor discovers that the restoration process was last tested 18 months ago. Given this finding, what should the IS auditor recommend?', 'Immediately suspend all incremental backups until a successful restoration test is performed.', 'Increase the frequency of full backups to compensate for the lack of restoration testing.', 'Schedule and execute a full restoration test as soon as possible, documenting the results.', 'Report the finding to the IT operations manager and request a justification for the lack of testing.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Schedule and execute a full restoration test as soon as possible, documenting the results.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRE