  ('CISA-00241', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Risk Management', 'During a review of an organization''s IT risk management framework, an IS auditor observes that the framework primarily focuses on technical vulnerabilities and threats but does not adequately address risks related to third-party service providers. The organization relies heavily on cloud-based services and outsourced IT support. What should the IS auditor recommend as the MOST critical improvement to the IT risk management framework?', 'Implement a formal process for conducting due diligence on all third-party service providers before engaging their services.', 'Develop a comprehensive disaster recovery plan that includes specific procedures for recovering from disruptions at third-party service providers.', 'Expand the risk management framework to include an assessment of the risks associated with third-party service providers, including their security controls and compliance with relevant regulations.', 'Require all third-party service providers to obtain independent security certifications, such as ISO 27001 or SOC 2, to demonstrate their security posture.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Expand the risk management framework to include an assessment of the risks associated with third-party service providers, including their security controls and compliance with relevant regulations.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, 