  ('CISA-00259', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Steering Committee Effectiveness', 'An IS auditor is reviewing the effectiveness of the IT steering committee at a large financial institution. The committee, composed of senior business executives and the CIO, meets quarterly to review IT project progress and approve new initiatives. The auditor observes that while the committee approves budgets and project plans, they rarely challenge the CIO''s recommendations or delve into the details of project risks and mitigation strategies. Which of the following actions should the IS auditor FIRST recommend to improve the IT steering committee''s effectiveness?', 'Implementing a formal risk management framework and requiring the CIO to present detailed risk assessments for each project.', 'Rotating committee membership to bring in fresh perspectives and expertise from different business units.', 'Conducting training for committee members on IT governance principles, project management methodologies, and risk assessment techniques.', 'Increasing the frequency of committee meetings to provide more opportunities for discussion and decision-making.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Conducting training for committee members on IT governance principles, project management methodologies, and risk assessment techniques.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and 