e or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00262', 2, 'Hard', 'Vendor Risk Management', 'An organization relies heavily on a third-party vendor for its cloud-based data storage. The contract with the vendor includes service level agreements (SLAs) for data availability and security. During an audit, the IS auditor discovers that the organization has not been actively monitoring the vendor''s compliance with these SLAs. While the vendor provides monthly reports on SLA performance, the organization simply files them without any formal review or analysis. Which of the following actions should the IS auditor recommend FIRST?', 'Negotiate more stringent SLAs with the vendor to improve data availability and security.', 'Implement a process for regularly reviewing and analyzing the vendor''s SLA performance reports.', 'Conduct an independent audit of the vendor''s security controls and data availability practices.', 'Develop a business continuity plan to address potential service disruptions from the vendor.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Implement a process for regularly reviewing and analyzing the vendor''s SLA performance reports.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  