  ('CISA-00281', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration & Integrity', 'An organization is migrating sensitive customer data to a new cloud-based data warehouse. During the migration process, the IS auditor discovers that Personally Identifiable Information (PII) is being transferred without encryption in transit. Which of the following actions should the IS auditor recommend FIRST?', 'Immediately halt the data migration process until appropriate encryption mechanisms are implemented.', 'Review the data migration plan to determine if encryption was intentionally omitted.', 'Report the incident to the organization''s legal counsel to determine potential regulatory implications.', 'Conduct a vulnerability assessment of the cloud infrastructure to identify other potential security weaknesses.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Immediately halt the data migration process until appropriate encryption mechanisms are implemented.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability f