  ('CISA-00296', 2, 'Medium', 'Resource Management', 'An IS auditor is reviewing the IT department''s project management practices. They observe that project managers frequently reallocate resources between projects to address unexpected issues, leading to delays and budget overruns across the portfolio. Which of the following should the IS auditor recommend **FIRST**?', 'Implement a formal resource management plan with clear allocation policies and escalation procedures.', 'Mandate that all project managers undergo advanced project management training.', 'Invest in a project portfolio management (PPM) tool to improve resource visibility.', 'Replace underperforming project managers with more experienced personnel.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Implement a formal resource management plan with clear allocation policies and escalation procedures.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis fo